According to the '''Life-span model of motivation''' the personal goals that individuals set are a function of the opportunities and challenges that are present in their social environment. Personal goals are an important determinant to the way individuals direct their development.<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2007-01-01|title=Personal project pursuit: Goals, action, and human flourishing.|url=http://psycnet.apa.org/psycinfo/2006-11798-000|journal=APA PsycNET|language=English}}</ref> The model introduces four key processes; channeling, choice, co-agency and compensation.<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Salmela-Aro|first=Katariina|date=2009-03-01|title=Personal goals and well-being during critical life transitions: The four C's—Channelling, choice, co-agency and compensation|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1040260809000045|journal=Advances in Life Course Research|series=Linked Lives and Self-Regulation. Lifespan - Life Course: Is it really the same?|volume=14|issue=1–2|pages=63–73|doi=10.1016/j.alcr.2009.03.003}}</ref>

== The 4 C's ==
Developmental trajectories are ''channeled'' by the [[social environment]], which represents the "opportunity space" for development.<ref name=":0" /> In addition, individuals are active agents in constructing their development, and hence make ''choices'' regarding their goals and commitments. Given that development occurs in a social context, others in the environment such as peers, family members or teachers have a role in ''co-regulation'' of development. And last, success and failures in personal goals and tasks serve as feedback and basis for ''compensation'' in order to optimize development.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.ch/books?hl=en&lr=&id=C0zbcXRqyMIC&oi=fnd&pg=PP1&dq=Developmental+Regulation+in+Adulthood:+Age-Normative+and+Sociostructural+Constraints+as+Adaptive+Challenges&ots=XfOdup072Z&sig=g96rMe7VkZQwL1MvcrT5PktzLLo#v=onepage&q=Developmental%20Regulation%20in%20Adulthood:%20Age-Normative%20and%20Sociostructural%20Constraints%20as%20Adaptive%20Challenges&f=false|title=Developmental Regulation in Adulthood: Age-Normative and Sociostructural Constraints as Adaptive Challenges|last=Heckhausen|first=Jutta|date=2006-06-22|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9780521027137|language=en}}</ref>

